# Cross-Platform Integration Standards

## Data Synchronization

- Implement bidirectional data synchronization between email platform and other systems
- Apply consistent field mapping across all integrated platforms
- Create conflict resolution protocols for data inconsistencies
- Implement real-time synchronization for critical customer data
- Document data flow diagrams for all integration points
- Apply proper error handling for synchronization failures

## Customer Identity Resolution

- Implement unified customer identification across platforms
- Create primary and secondary identity resolution methods
- Apply deterministic and probabilistic matching techniques
- Implement proper privacy controls for identity resolution
- Document identity resolution logic and success rates
- Create fallback mechanisms for unresolved identities

## Event Handling

- Implement standardized event schema across platforms
- Create centralized event collection and distribution
- Apply consistent event naming conventions
- Implement event validation and sanitization
- Document event taxonomy for cross-platform actions
- Create event handling failure recovery mechanisms

## Unified Segmentation

- Create segments that incorporate data from multiple sources
- Implement segment synchronization across platforms
- Apply consistent segment naming conventions
- Document segment qualification criteria across systems
- Create segment membership reconciliation processes
- Implement segment analytics across platforms

## Testing and Monitoring

- Create comprehensive integration test suites
- Implement real-time monitoring of integration points
- Apply alerting for integration failures or anomalies
- Create integration health dashboards
- Document integration failure recovery procedures
- Implement periodic integration verification processes

